        "description": "Trying to do an inner join style filter on an open_dataset, and R crashes, but not reliably the first time. Sometimes takes a couple of tries until it does.\r\n\r\nReprex follows.\r\n\r\n------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nlibrary (arrow)\r\nlibrary (dplyr)\r\nlibrary (tidyr)\r\n\r\nDataSet <- expand_grid (A = 1:10, B = 1:10, C = 1:10000) %>%\r\n\u00a0 group_by (A, B)\r\nwrite_dataset(DataSet, \"TestBreakData\")\r\n\r\nfor (DoThisUntilItBreaks in 1:100) {\r\n\u00a0 message (DoThisUntilItBreaks)\r\n\u00a0 D2 <- open_dataset(\"TestBreakData\") %>% inner_join (data.frame (A=1L, B=1:5)) %>% collect\r\n}",
